    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f0cdb3e0_f02e9992",
        "filename": "src/gpu/dawn/GrDawnOpsRenderPass.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 111,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-12T15:51:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So generally what this is used for is when we have a single texture atlas (usually for fonts). We have a max size for the atlas so if a batch of text draws can\u0027t all fit into the atlas we need to break up the draws. So first we upload all the text needed for draws 1...k. Then we inline upload new data to the same atlas and do draws k+1...N.\n\nSo if you don\u0027t do the inline upload, then draws k+1...N will use masks from the first set incorrectly. If you do the inline upload before the draws 1....k then you may have draws in 1...k that are using masks from the second set instead of their own.\n\nThe usual failure case looks like the wrong glyph being used for a given draw.",
      "parentUuid": "99005171_ab1bfc29",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 111,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 111,
        "endChar": 28
      },
      "revId": "5ef17204d443cb7dad9148abecb03aa618326104",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
