      "writtenOn": "2020-05-11T18:22:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So I think the correct thing to do here would be to pass GrCaps into this function and use the readpixels supported query on there to see if we can do a readPixels or not. If not we just return.\n\nIn the short term if you don\u0027t want to put that into this change, I would replace the assert here with a REPORTER_ASSERT so it documents exactly where the failure is.\n\nOn a side note, I am kind of surprised this is failing. I thought the thing we couldn\u0027t readpixels from in dawn was a GrBackendRenderTarget because all we pass in was the view. But this is a case where we are passing in a GrBackendTexture so we do have the actual backend object even if it is only stored as a GrRenderTarget. Shouldn\u0027t this be able to work?",
      "parentUuid": "29be91fa_3892ebd4",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 852,
