        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-12T15:51:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes Brian is once again working on trying to remove that code path, so I don\u0027t think it is worth any effort making sure it works \"better\" than it does today.\n\nLike I said I think the best fix for this is to call GrCaps::surfaceSupportsReadPixels(GrSurface*), before the readPixels here and return if it is not supported. Since the SkSurface was created with a GrBackendTexture the inner GrSurfaceProxy should be instantiated for you to get the GrSurface out.\n\nIn the very short term I\u0027m also fine with putting a REPORTER_ASSERT around the read pixels return value so that the test isn\u0027t crashing anymore. And then come back through and add the above fix for the test to actually pass.",
      "parentUuid": "9795ce05_9fc3fa81",
